metadata.name: "Pyramid Complex" - from LoveBux LABS #13
metadata.description:
"PYRAMID COMPLEX" - A Temple for YOU

The pharaohs and ceremonial kings of the past once raised mausoleums and temple complexes to honor their Gods, to perpetuate their memory among the people, and to preserve their bodies and riches for use in the afterlife. 

Good news! 

The scientists at LOVEBUX LABS, can offer you a custom built funerary temple in the Metaverse. 

This immutable self constructing pyramid complex is well suited to be the resting place for PFP projects that went nowhere, or any “ape ins” or crypto-blunders that should have 'mooned' but went to zero instead.

Let these restless digital ghosts find peace in a 5 dimensional non-Euclidian palace, and perhaps their memories will sweeten with time. Or you could also make this your future palace for ships unsailed, unuttered dreams or narcissistic ambitions —it’s up to you.

But whatever your aims - please enjoy your own unique citadel to rule over in splendor, and enshrine there... whatever suits your royal whims!

LoveBux Labs
12/4/21

metadata.name: A long starry night #14
metadata.description:
This generative landscape is animated, some animations are very slow and take around 2 hours to loop.
This experience is best viewed fullscreen (click 'open' and go fullscreen) between FHD and QHD resolutions.

Press 'K' on the keyboard to go in the exploration mode. There you can drag the view with touch or mouse and orbit around stellar cluster.
Press 'K' again to embark on a travel following a celestial object.
Press 'SPACE' keyboard to take a screenshot (PNG) at current resolution.

attributes.name: In tribute to the science star

metadata.name: Mirror Mirror #120
metadata.description:
Stare into the abyss with endlessly repeating forms twisting into the infinity defined by perlin randomness. This project is inspired by early childhood memories looking into two mirrors and playing with reflections forever.

Mirror Mirror is a generative project with a digital output, but it has a second life as a physical IRL object that can be cut from 12 layers of wood or plotted on paper.

24 free physicals will be attached at random to mints.
Learn more about physicals: https://alleditions.art/p/mirrormirror

SPECIAL FEATURES
- Shift-P: exports a PNG
- Shift-E: explodes the layers
- Shift-S: Exports an SVG
- A, S, D, & W: skew the layers
- ?screws=true: add some holes for Chicago screws
